20 percent rule	the rule that, when 20 percent or more of a group’s membership is of a particular minority, acts of discrimination against that minority exists	hint	
Active listening 	process of paraphrasing the other’s ideas or statements, including the provision of feedback about nonverbal messages	hint	
Burelle’s Broadcast Database 	a large and comprehensive print and broadcast media directory	hint	
Causal relationship 	relationship between two events that suggests the first event is responsible for the second event happening	hint	
Dowjones News/Retrieval	this database provides business-related information.  This includes company and industry news, economic and financial news, and stock trading information.	hint	
Either-this-or-that reasoning 	an argument that suggests to a listener that there are only two alternatives from which to make a decision.  This is often a fallacy as there are generally more than two alternatives available.	hint	
Electronic database 	an information source that may be accessed via the internet by visiting a particular site	hint	
Electronic journal	a scholarly reference work that is published on and accessed via the internet	hint	
Empathic listening	a process of receiving information in which the receiver attempts to understand what is being said by a source from that person’s prospective	hint	
Encyclopedias on disc	a source of general information that may be accessed via a computer and a compact disk	hint	
ERIC	the educational resources information center is a national system that provides access to an extensive body of education literature.	hint	
Evaluative listening 	a process of receiving information in which the receiver attempts to understand what is being said by considering it through his or her experience and knowledge base	hint	
Fact 	statement about an observation that can be demonstrated to be true	hint	
Fallacies	an error in the reasoning process that makes an argument unsound	
Faulty comparison	an error in the reasoning process where two or more things are thought to be like each other, but are not	hint	
Home page 	the primary page of an internet website	hint	
Inference 	a guess; a judgement, based upon observational data, about the meaning of those data	hint	
Internet search engine	these sites provide key word searches of the internet for sites that include information about the key words presented for the search	hint	
LEXIS/NEXIS 	an interdisciplinary , full-text database that includes newspapers, journals, wire services, newsletters, company reports, case law, government documents, transcripts of broadcasts, and selected reference materials	hint	
Online catalog 	a database of a library’s holdings, accessed by a computer	hint	
Overgeneralization 	a conclusion that results when data for some reason are not strong enough to support it	hint	
Personal prejudice 	a error in reasoning about an issue that has its basis in biases the individual employs in the in the process	hint	
Question of cause 	a problem for group discussion that requires the group to examine data and evidence to determine the cause of the particular situation or issue	hint	
Question of definition 	a problem for group discussion that requires the group to examine data and evidence to discover the meaning or significance of the issue	hint	
Question of fact 	a discussion issue that does not involve value decisions or policies and that can be resolved to collecting information that addresses the issue	hint	
Question of policy 	a problem for group discussion that requires the group to examine data and evidence to recommend a course of action to resolve or handle a particular situation or issue	hint	
Question of value 	a problem for group discussion that requires the group to examine data and evidence to determine the desirability or preference of the group regarding a particular situation or issue	hint	
Sensing 	the act of receiving stimuli through the five senses	hint	
Thinking for yourself 	independent consideration of an issue based on a person’s own understanding of the issue, data, and reasoning process	hint	
